</table>
</div>
<p>A highly recommended combination encompassing the best scenery the Fjord Norway region has to offer – starting in the fjordside village of <a data-udi="umb://document/a09d8dda0d4f48d68be229cdaeb2f377" href="/{localLink:umb://document/a09d8dda0d4f48d68be229cdaeb2f377}" title="Balestrand">Balestrand</a> on the mighty Sognefjord, you will have an opportunity to travel on the famous Flåm railway or visit Fjaerland with its Glacier Museum. From here, your included transfer will take you over the magical Gauler Mountains to <a data-udi="umb://document/14f6ab787ad2493ab23ce60aa9f14e6a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/14f6ab787ad2493ab23ce60aa9f14e6a}" title="Loen">Loen</a> on the Nordfjord with its spectacular glacier and sparkling lakes. The areas that surround Loen are arguably home to the fjords’ greatest display of natural beauty and there are good walking opportunities here especially now with the addition of the new Skylift cable-car. The last leg of your journey takes you to the Atlantic Coast and the Art Nouveau city of Ålesund, where regular boats take visitors to the surrounding small islands and fishing skerries. An Inghams Representative will be on hand in Balestrand and Loen.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Extend your stay</strong> Guests may choose to add a stay in colourful Bergen or the picturesque village of Ulvik on the Hardangerfjord at the start of their holiday. Guests adding Bergen will travel to Balestrand on coastal express boat, after their stay in the city, whilst guests who choose to add Ulvik will enjoy a scenic transfer by minibus via Voss.</p>
<p><strong>Pre-book your excursions</strong> in Balestrand, Loen and Ålesund </p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<p><strong>Day 1 (Monday or Friday) |</strong> Fly to Bergen airport and transfer to Balestrand on the Sognefjord, known as ‘King of the Fjords’ for being the longest and deepest fjord in Norway and stretching over 200km. Exploring this fjord is a real treat with an opportunity to enjoy picturesque boat trips, gentle walking routes along the shore, the impressive Jøstedal glacier and the world’s steepest gauge railway from Flåm.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Day 4 or 5 (Friday or Monday)</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>A spectacular 3 hour drive over the magical Gauler mountains to Loen on the Nordfjord, your base for the next 3 or 4 nights. Trips to the famous Geiranger Fjord or to the emerald lakes and ice-blue glaciers of the Lodal and Briksdal valleys are a must and the new Skylift cable-car from the village provides further exploring opportunities with several walking trails at the top, not to mention the views. The spa and pool facilities at the Hotel Alexandra provide a great setting to relax and unwind after your day out.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Day 8 (Monday or Friday)</strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Day 8 Another scenic transfer to the vibrant Art Nouveau city of Ålesund allows you to sit back and admire the spectacular scenery of the Nordfjord and Sunnmøre regions up close. Once in Ålesund, explore its museums, discover its interesting architecture and surrounding islands or simply take a stroll along its pretty waterfront.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Day 11 or 12 (Friday or Monday) </strong></p>
<p> </p>
<p>Return by shuttle to Ålesund airport for your flight back to the UK. </p>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>Optional 4th centre</strong></p>
<p><strong><a href="/%7blocalLink:umb:/document/d517b2c21fa94eb096a3bcb6b7e933c5%7d">Bergen</a></strong></p>
<p>For guests extending their holiday with 3 or 4 nights in Bergen at the start of their holiday, the 'Bergen Card' is a great value way to explore this colourful city, with its many galleries, museums, thriving fish and flower markets. Or visit one of the classical concerts, the large park and gardens or the Fløiban funicular railway for stunning views. Bergen Cards are available to purchase locally a 24, 48 or 72 hour period, from £28 per person. Your transfer to Balestrand is by 4-hr coastal express boat from Bergen (departure approx. 8:00 or 16:30).</p>
<p><strong><a href="/%7blocalLink:umb:/document/5cc2f02c69b84f1daac6b84a0a98c6d2%7d">Ulvik</a> </strong></p>
<p>For guests extending their holiday with 3 or 4 nights in Ulvik at the start of their holdiay, transfers to Balestrand are a scenic 3 hours drive and short ferry ride (included).  In Ulvik, guests have chance to explore the wonderful Hardangerfjord, known as the 'Orchard of Norway' for its fruit and cherry blossoms.  An excursion to the Eidfjord and impressive Vøringfossen waterfalls can be done by express boat. Alternatively, guests can simply relax in the serene setting of the fjordside garden or spa of the Hotel Brakanes, or explore by foot on one of the nearby walking trails.</p>
</div>
<div><em> </em></div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>What's Included</h2>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li>•Return flight from the UK to Bergen and back from Ålesund</li>
<li>•Scenic transfers to and from the airport and between each resort*</li>
<li>•Accommodation with private facilities throughout</li>
<li>•Half board meals included in Balestrand (Hotel Kviknes only) &amp; Loen and Ulvik if extending to 14 nights</li>
<li>•Bed &amp; Breakfast in Ålesund &amp; Balestrand (Hotel Midtnes only) and Bergen if extending to 14 nights</li>
</ul>
<p>*For guests arriving into Bergen on indirect flights via Amsterdam, transfers from Bergen airport to Balestrand will be by minibus. For all other guests, transfers will be by coastal express boat (transfer from airport to boat quay included)</p>
</div>
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Inghams Plus</h2>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li>•Early Booking Offer: Save up to £40 per couple (ends 31 Mar) Discount included in the prices shown</li>
<li>•Inghams Rep service in Balestrand and Loen (and Bergen if extending to 14 nights)</li>
<li>•Inghams 'Meet &amp; Greet' service in Ålesund centre and visiting rep service in Ulvik (if extending to 14 nights)</li>
<li>*Early Booking Discount is based on 'Superior Hotels' holiday</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Accommodation</h2>
<p> </p>
<p><strong>'Standard Hotels'</strong></p>
<p>Balestrand <a data-udi="umb://document/e6e72ed8f54b4b799df9821bf732b69d" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/balestrand/midtnes-hotel" title="Midtnes Hotel">Hotel Midtnes</a> **+</p>
<p>Loen <a data-udi="umb://document/7780b99803294b0f8a9519ed836b9830" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/loen/loenfjord-hotel" title="Loenfjord Hotel">Hotel Loenfjord</a> ***+</p>
<p>Alesund <a data-udi="umb://document/89e354afa6824ae197da03b9604055e7" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/alesund/first-hotel-atlantica" title="First Hotel Atlantica">First Hotel Atlantica</a> ***+</p>
<p><strong>OR</strong></p>
<p><strong>'Superior Hotels' </strong></p>
<p>Balestrand <a data-udi="umb://document/d26dcba440054402b9ccfe7166c1ad56" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/balestrand/kviknes-hotel" title="Kviknes Hotel">Hotel Kviknes</a> **** </p>
<p>Loen <a data-udi="umb://document/fbdb2d63e0f24d7fb8fbb7a20fdd9578" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/loen/alexandra-hotel" title="Alexandra Hotel">Hotel Alexandra</a> ****+ </p>
<p>Ålesund <a data-udi="umb://document/7ce188510b05444696b765f7f5cc643b" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/norway/alesund/hotel-brosundet" title="Hotel Brosundet">Hotel Brosundet</a> **** </p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="g6">
<div class="white_box_shadow">
<h2>Departure Dates &amp; Prices for 2019</h2>
<p> </p>
<ul>
<li>•Depart Monday, 11 nights = <span>4 nights Balestrand, 3 nights Loen, 4 nights Ålesund</span></li>
<li>•Depart Friday, 10 nights = <span>3 nights Balestrand, 4 nights Loen, 3 nights Ålesund</span></li>
<li>•Prices from £1,299 in standard hotels</li>
<li>•Prices from £1,699 in superior hotels</li>
</ul>
</div>
